4. HIGH-LEVEL ARCHITECTURE
   The reporting system is divided into six core modules:

5. Reporter Engine

6. Event Collector

7. Asset Collector

8. Data Serializer

9. AI Error Analyzer

10. HTML Renderer

Each module has a defined responsibility to ensure separation of concerns and scalability.

---

5. MODULE DESCRIPTIONS

5.1 Reporter Engine

* Implements Playwright’s reporter interface
* Receives callbacks: onBegin, onTestBegin, onStepBegin, onStepEnd, onTestEnd, onEnd
* Converts raw Playwright events into structured metadata
* Triggers asset collection

5.2 Event Collector

* Collects details such as:
  test name, suite name, steps, expectations, timestamps, retries
* Maintains internal model for every test
* Stores logs and trace information

5.3 Asset Collector

* Saves screenshots at failure
* Saves video paths
* Saves traces if enabled
* Organizes assets into the output folder structure

5.4 Data Serializer

* Converts in-memory JSON model into physical JSON files
* Writes test results, metadata, and attachment indexes
* Ensures stable schema for UI rendering

5.5 AI Error Analyzer

* Reads exceptions
* Classifies them into categories:
  LocatorNotFound, Timeout, VisibilityError, AssertionError, NetworkError
* Provides probable root cause
* Suggests recommended fix
* Enhances error readability

5.6 HTML Renderer

* Generates HTML pages
* Loads results.json
* Displays dashboards, charts, and detailed test pages
* Embeds screenshots and videos
* Human-friendly and interactive UI

---

6. WORKFLOW DESCRIPTION

Test Start → Reporter Engine Captures Event → Event Collector Structures Data →
Asset Collector Saves Files → JSON Serializer Writes Data → Reporter Completes →
HTML Renderer Generates UI → Final Report Available

